      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The feature of the day now and LADIES PRO (3) gets the nod. She was far too good in the Belmont Oaks when rounding them up and putting them to the sword with strong late sectionals. Pike can sit closer this time and she showed an electric turn of foot last time out. Can go back-to-back. WESTBOUND (1) landed the knockout blow in the Aquanita Stakes where he was just too good. This may set up differently with a small field engaged, but the inside draw is a big tick and he rates highly on his latest effort. SPECIAL COUNSEL (2) finished behind WESTBOUND last start in the Aquanita and shouldn't be as far back today with a smaller field engaged. Improving nicely as he steps out in distance and he won't be far away. PONY UP (4) can sit up front from the outset and make every post a winner. AUTUMN GEM (6) can sneak into the finish.",
